  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Also, they heard the atrocities of the German army.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "They kind of stuck.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Didn't know which direction to go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "The Zionists encouraged to leave.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Some young people left, and they went to Israel in some way.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Everything changed the 17th of September, when Hitler made a pact with Stalin, and the Russian army occupied our area, what you call Eastern Poland, which is Western Ukraine, and incorporate that into the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "All the total population looked at the Russian army, the Red Army, as liberators.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Also, some of the Poles and mostly Ukrainians, nationalistic, were not very happy, but they accepted the fact that it was a liberation, a uniting of Western Ukraine and Eastern Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "The Polish people were in the-- in the middle because Hitler attacked them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "They didn't know which direction to go 'cause this is only 19 years ago where the new Poland is established after so many years of the Czar, Russian empire occupation.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "When the Russian army came in, the-- I must say that the Russian soldiers were very well behaved, very compassionate.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Also, they didn't have any material things because our area was like a free enterprise that you could buy anything, the same as in America.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "The people under the Soviet regime in Russia didn't have those luxuries.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the soldiers who had some money or got some money were good clients.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they came in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They bought everything they could find.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This didn't last too long because right behind the Russian army came in what you call the propaganda commissars, with some Russian people trying to install a-- a-- a Soviet administration, where they nationalized all of the businesses.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my folks wound up working at a distribution center.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
